Description: Fragment of plaster figure. Possibly fragment of ithyphallic figure?
Curator's comments: Similar figurines made from identical limestone found in excavated contexts at Naukratis. Probably fragment of tambour.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (CE.191) (Phase 3)
Acquisition notes: aquired before 1965, probably from Naukratis in the 1880's
